  <span id="freeText10457717371646277114" style="display:none">It is a very hypnotic tale. I was really absorbed into the story-line and I felt I had time-traveled to the 17th-century Persian myself. I really adore the courage of the unnamed main character who still manage to move on after each of the misfortunes that had befallen her. This story also shows how a girl matures into a women and how her dreams evolve with time. I also got the inside into the culture of Shia muslim, which I had never know. I love how the narrator is so passionate about carpet making, and I believe from now onwards I would never view a carpet as I used to see. <br />I am glad that I picked this book from the shelves of the bookstores, which was really random. </span>
