<span id="freeTextContainer13694505783325841754">Blood of Flowers<br/><br/>377 pages, almost all of them grim. <br/><br/>A rich man gets all the<a class='jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction'>(view spoiler)</a><span class='spoilerContainer' style='display: none'>[ young women he wants, as disposable sex toys.  <a class='jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction'>(hide spoiler)</a>]</span><br/><br/>To earn money you must have something to sell, and the ability to sell it and not get <a class='jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction'>(view spoiler)</a><span class='spoilerContainer' style='display: none'>[cheated. <a class='jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction'>(hide spoiler)</a>]</span> <br/><br/>It&apos;s a short step from broke to debased, hungry, tired, weak, miserable, filthy, cold, wet, sick, … .<br/><br/>Set in Persia in the 1620s; that sort of grimness is neither long ago nor far away. <br/><br/>Opulence creates squalor, then and n</span>
  <span id="freeText13694505783325841754" style="display:none">Blood of Flowers<br /><br />377 pages, almost all of them grim. <br /><br />A rich man gets all the<a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[ young women he wants, as disposable sex toys.  <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span><br /><br />To earn money you must have something to sell, and the ability to sell it and not get <a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[cheated. <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span> <br /><br />It's a short step from broke to debased, hungry, tired, weak, miserable, filthy, cold, wet, sick, … .<br /><br />Set in Persia in the 1620s; that sort of grimness is neither long ago nor far away. <br /><br />Opulence creates squalor, then and now.<br /><br />Too true to be good.<br /><br />The author did her homework on the time and place. She cites some sources:<br /><br />Novelist and writing teacher Sandra Scofield (p. 370)<br /><a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="https://www.goodreads.com/author/list/165179.Sandra_Scofield">https://www.goodreads.com/author/list...</a> <br /><br />Iran scholar Roger M. Savory (p. 373)<br /><a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="https://www.goodreads.com/author/list/415189.Roger_M_Savory">https://www.goodreads.com/author/list...</a> <br /><br />Thomas Herbert, who travelled to Persia in 1627-1629 (p. 373)<br /><a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/7481092-travels-in-persia">https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/7...</a> <br /><br />Eskandar Monshi, Shah Abbas's official historian (p. 374)<br /><a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/182273.The_History_of_Shaah_Abb_s_the_Great">https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/1...</a> <br /><br />John Chardin, who travelled in Persia 1673-1677 (p. 374)<br /><a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="https://www.goodreads.com/author/list/330894.John_Chardin">https://www.goodreads.com/author/list...</a> <br /><br />Traditional Crafts of Persia, Hans E. Wulff (p. 375)<br /><a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/6292139-traditional-crafts-of-persia">https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/6...</a> <br /><br />Ties that Bind: A Social History of the Iranian Carpet, Leonard M. Helfgott (p. 375)<br /><a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/3361028-ties-that-bind">https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/3...</a> <br /><br />Images of Paradise in Islamic Art, Sheila S. Blair, ed. (p. 375)<br /><a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/15279462-images-of-paradise-in-islamic-art">https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/1...</a> <br /><br />Law of Desire: Temporary Marriage in Shi'i Iran, Shahla Haeri (p. 375)<br /><a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="https://www.goodreads.com/author/list/96466.Shahla_Haeri">https://www.goodreads.com/author/list...</a> <br /><br />The Arabian Nights (p. 376)<br /><a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/93101.The_Arabian_Nights">https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/9...</a> <br /><br />Nizami Ganjavi, 12th-century poet, /Haft Paykar (Seven Portraits)/ and Layla and Majnoon (p. 376)<br /><a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="https://www.goodreads.com/author/list/91847.Nizami_Ganjavi?page=1&amp;per_page=99">https://www.goodreads.com/author/list...</a> <br /><br />Henri Masse, Persian Beliefs and Customs (p. 376)<br /><a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="https://www.goodreads.com/author/list/3166775.Henri_Masse">https://www.goodreads.com/author/list...</a> <br /><br />Layla and Majnun, translated by Rudolf Gelpke (p. 376)<br /><a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="https://www.goodreads.com/author/list/2222329.Rudolf_Gelpke">https://www.goodreads.com/author/list...</a> <br /><br />Haft Paykar (Seven Portraits), translated by Julie Scott Meisami (p. 376)<br /><a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="https://www.goodreads.com/author/list/506804.Julie_Scott_Meisami">https://www.goodreads.com/author/list...</a> <br /><br />Illahi-Nama (Book of God), Farid al-Din Attar, transl. John Andrew Boyle (p. 376)<br /><a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="https://www.goodreads.com/author/list/7457124.Attar_of_Nishapur">https://www.goodreads.com/author/list...</a> <br /><br />A Two-Colored Brocade: The Images of Persian Poetry, Annemarie Schimmel (p. 377)<br /><a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/133889.A_Two_Colored_Brocade">https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/1...</a> <br /><br />A Survey of Persian Art, Arthur Upham Pope (p. 377)<br /><a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="https://www.goodreads.com/author/list/156817.Arthur_Upham_Pope">https://www.goodreads.com/author/list...</a></span>
