<div id="review_202234027" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/202234027" />
    <a title="Gaijinmama" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/917504-gaijinmama"><img alt="Gaijinmama" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1203383974p2/917504.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/202234027?book_show_action=true">May 27, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Gaijinmama" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Gaijinmama" href="/user/show/917504-gaijinmama">Gaijinmama</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780755334216" href="/book/show/2049670.The_Blood_of_Flowers">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/917504-gaijinmama?shelf=fiction">fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/917504-gaijinmama?shelf=historical-fiction">historical-fiction</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer202234027" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16863802491464704905">This book has sat on my shelf for around three or four years. The title fits a Reading Challenge I&apos;m doing, but more importantly, in the past year or two a few lovely, brilliant, fierce Iranian women have crossed my path and made my world a much more interesting place. They&apos;re all very different people, and have made me more aware of the rich history and ethnic/ cultural diversity of Iran. <br/>In short, the timing was right and this book really resonated with me.<br/>I connected with the narrator, too, e</span>
  <span id="freeText16863802491464704905" style="display:none">This book has sat on my shelf for around three or four years. The title fits a Reading Challenge I'm doing, but more importantly, in the past year or two a few lovely, brilliant, fierce Iranian women have crossed my path and made my world a much more interesting place. They're all very different people, and have made me more aware of the rich history and ethnic/ cultural diversity of Iran. <br />In short, the timing was right and this book really resonated with me.<br />I connected with the narrator, too, even though we readers never learn her name. That makes it easier, I suppose, for her to represent every teenage girl who just can't bring herself to keep her mouth shut and play the role society has set for her. (That said, I fully recognize that I come from a place of much greater freedom and privilege than she does. The 17th century was not a great place to be poor and female.<br />In particular, there's a scene (I won't spoil) that describes perfectly how cruel women can be to each other in order to protect what advantages we happen to have. My heart breaks that we don't support and have each others' backs more in this world.<br />Finally, as a lover of yarn and thread crafts, I am fascinated by the beautiful descriptions of the handmade carpets that provide vivid color to every page of this book. And don't even get me started on the food...my mouth waters just remembering it!<br /><br />Read, enjoy, savor, maybe cry a little at the injustice the narrator faces, and be transported!<br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="16863802491464704905" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


